article.description: John Meeks posted 19 points as Bucknell defeated Holy Cross 75-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Meeks scores 19 to carry Bucknell past Holy Cross 75-60
article.linkText: Meeks scores 19 to carry Bucknell past Holy Cross 75-60
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- John Meeks posted 19 points as Bucknell defeated Holy Cross 75-60 on Saturday. Andrew Funk had 17 points and seven rebounds for Bucknell (7-10, 3-1 Patriot League). Avi Toomer added 13 points. Bruce Moore had 12 points for the hosts. The Bison forced a season-high 22 turnovers. Drew Lowder had 21 points for the Crusaders (2-15, 1-3). He also had seven turnovers but only two assists. Austin Butler added 17 points. Connor Niego had 11 points and 10 rebounds. Bucknell plays American on the road on Wednesday. Holy Cross matches up against Army at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
